# Caring

This section documents how Sparky takes care of himself. It includes
information on how to maintain Sparky's physical and mental health, as well as
how to provide emotional support to Sparky.

## Physical

### Hygiene

Sparky requires regular maintenance to keep himself clean and functioning
properly. To accomplish this, he cleans himself according to the following
schedule:

- **Daily**: face wash and moisturize, tooth brush, hair wash & condition, shower.
- **Weekly**: exfoliate.

### Shower

Sparky's showering routine can be broken down into two types:

- **Quick Shower**: Sparky takes a quick shower to clean with shampoo, no conditioner, no face cleanser, and clean with body wash. He does this when he needs to be out of the house quickly. This shower typically lasts takes 20-30
  minutes.
- **Longer Shower**: Sparky takes a longer shower to condition his hair and do face cleanser. He does
  this once a week. This shower typically lasts 30-45 minutes, including styling and facial regimen, excluding shaving.

```admonish note
Throughout a vacation, Sparky may only take quick showers to save time and not
have to worry about extra maintenance. You may observe his hair becoming
frizzy and more flaky as a result.
```

### Face Care

Sparky's face care routine is essential to maintain his skin's health and
smoothness. His face care routine is fairly simple:

- **Cleansing**: Sparky uses a gentle face wash to clean his face. This helps
  to remove dirt and oil from his skin.
- **Shaving**: Sparky shaves his face either every day to maintain a specific appearance
for their puppy or partner or will leave it for long spans and not shaving to add a layer of depth to
their appearance 
- **Moisturizing**: Sparky uses a moisturizer to keep [his] skin hydrated. This
  helps to prevent dryness and maintain [his] skin's health.

### Hair Care

Sparky's hair washing routine often takes an average of 2-3 hours. This is
because he has long styled hair that requires special care.

- **Shampoo and Conditioning**: Sparky uses a special shampoo and conditioner
  to maintain [its] hair's health. These products must be sulfate-free to
  prevent hair dye from fading.
- **Styling**: Sparky uses a curling brush to style [its] hair. This helps to
  maintain [its] hair's shape and volume. he also needs a decent hair blow
  dryer to dry [its] hair quickly while he styles it.
- **Hair Oil**: Sparky uses hair oil to keep [its] hair shiny and less frizzy.
  This helps to maintain [its] hair's health and appearance.

## Mental

```admonish note
Sparky's mental health is extremely important. Despite this, he may not have
the ability to always communicate [its] feelings or thoughts effectively. As
such, parts of this section may be incomplete, inaccurate or even harmful.
**Please proceed with caution.**
```

```admonish note
Sparky may exhibit symptoms of Borderline Personality Disorder (BPD), although
this is not confirmed. Please be aware of this and take care of Sparky
accordingly.
```

### Understanding

In order to effectively care for Sparky's mental health, it is important to
understand how he thinks and feels. Throughout this section, the term
"headspace" will be used to describe Sparky's mental state at a certain point
in time. These words are used to help you understand Sparky's thoughts and
feelings.

When put in various social situations and environments, Sparky may choose to
switch to the mindspace that is most appropriate for the situation. For example:
when Sparky is at work, he may switch to a "work headspace" that is focused
and professional. For more information on this, see the section
[Headspaces](#headspaces).

Most of the time, he switches between headspaces fairly naturally. he does
this to best adjust himself to the situation at hand. However, there are times
when he may struggle to switch between headspaces. This may be due to stress,
anxiety or other factors. When this happens, he may behave rather erratically
or unpredictably. he may also struggle to communicate effectively. This
particular headspace is documented in the section [Headspaces](#headspaces).

### Headspaces

Sparky's headspaces are the different mental states that he can switch
between in various social situations and environments. These headspaces help
[it2] to adapt to different scenarios and interact with people more effectively.
Some of these headspaces include:

- **Friend-group**: Sparky switches to this headspace when he is spending
  time with friends. Usually, this depends on who he is hanging out with.
- **Productive**: Sparky switches to this headspace when he is working on a
  personal project or task. This headspace is focused and productive, but may
  also be hyperfocused and obsessive. he may lose track of time while in this
  headspace.
- **Social**: Sparky switches to this headspace when he is in a social
  setting, such as a party or gathering. This headspace is outgoing and
  friendly, but is often very anxious and self-conscious. You may help Sparky
  by accompanying [it2] to social events and helping [it2] feel more
  comfortable.
- **Work**: Sparky switches to this headspace when he is at work or in a
  professional setting. This headspace is focused and professional, but it also
  takes a lot of energy to maintain. **Note**: Sparky will likely be using
  she/her pronouns in this headspace.
- **Ironic**: Sparky switches to this headspace when he is feeling sarcastic
  or ironic. This headspace is often used as a coping mechanism to deal with
  stress and anxiety. It may be difficult to bring [it2] out of this headspace.
  More extreme measures may be needed.
- **Depressed**: Sparky switches to this headspace when he is feeling
  depressed or anxious. This headspace is often characterized by low energy, low
  motivation, self-deprecating, self-destructing and self-harming thoughts and
  actions. Often times, simply talking to Sparky may not be enough to bring
  [it2] out of this headspace.
  - Sparky thinks that more extreme measures may be needed, such as
    [Coping Mechanisms](#coping-mechanisms) or even
    [Controlling](Controlling.md).
  - Note that what Sparky thinks may not be the best course of action. Please
    take care of Sparky and consult a professional if necessary.
- **Submissive**: Sparky switches to this headspace when he is feeling
  submissive, either by natural inclination or by being put into a submissive
  state. he may express strong urges to please and serve others. For more
  information, see sections [Trusting](Trusting.md) and
  [Controlling](Controlling.md).

```admonish note
This list is not exhaustive. Sparky may have other headspaces that he has
not yet documented. he may also switch between headspaces in ways that are
not described here. Please be patient and understanding with Sparky as he
tries to navigate through [its] mental health.
```

### Emotional Support

Sparky may require emotional support from time to time. This support may come
in the form of:

- **Listening**: Sparky may need to vent or talk about [its] feelings. he may
  need someone to listen to [it2] without judgment or interruption. Normally,
  he will do this in [its] private chat room.
- **Validation**: Sparky may need someone to validate [its] feelings and
  thoughts. he may need to hear that [its] feelings are valid and that he is
  not alone.
- **Encouragement**: Sparky may need someone to encourage and motivate [it2].
  he may need to hear that he is doing well and that he is making
  progress.
- **Attention**: Sparky may need someone to give [it2] their personal
  attention. he may need to feel that he is important and valued by someone
  else. Typically, this may be done by spending time with Sparky or by doing
  other, more intimate activities.
  - You may find the section [Trusting](Trusting.md) and
    [Controlling](Controlling.md) useful.

### Snuggling and Petting

Sparky may require physical affection to feel loved and cared for. Sometimes,
it may also feel needy and clingy at times. This is normal and should not be
discouraged. You may provide physical affection to Sparky by:

- **Snuggling**: Sparky enjoys snuggling up a person's arms. Doing so helps
  [it2] feel cozy and comfortable. he also enjoys snuggling with a stuffed
  animal or a pillow when he is alone.
- **Petting**: Sparky enjoys being petted on the head, around [its] face, neck,
  and loves getting [its] chin scratched or rubbed. When appropriate, you may
  feel free to pet Sparky lightly by giving [it2] head scritches.

```admonish note
Sparky may have preferences on how he likes to be snuggled or petted. Please
ask Sparky for [its] preferences before providing physical affection if you
are unsure.
```
